{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"fbfad774-585d-4002-aaa2-58016ba4ca6f","content":"Here's the skip attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod, Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test, Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test, Skip(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic async Task MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nAll four frameworks will report these as **skipped/ignored** (not failed) in test results, and the reason string appears in the test output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ac3e8cc1-307a-4839-97c2-8944f283ac42","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to skip tests with a reason message in MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. This is a straightforward knowledge question about test framework attributes. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":322,"requestId":"CFC0:12531F:14A4329:17E71B3:69EC1324"},"id":"46b426bd-ac57-412e-84ed-f84f7cb123c9","timestamp":"2026-04-25T01:04:42.416Z","parentId":"7e450ef6-1782-46e2-affd-537311bce329"}
